 commutes. Filling in the map F(i, j)\xrightarrow {F(i, f)} F(i, j'), the top
 triangle is the definition of \operatorname *{lim}_J, while the bottom square is
 by construction of the functorial action of colimits.

The J-indexed limit and colimit functors are
characterized as right and left adjoints, respectively, of the
constant diagram functor C\xrightarrow {\Delta } C^J:




