  \end {tikzcd}


 is a pullback square and f is monic, then so is \pi _C.

Let Z\overset {h,k}{\rightrightarrows } P be parallel arrows such that \pi _Ch = \pi _Ck. Then
  f\pi _b h = g\pi _c h = g\pi _c k = f\pi _b k, so since f is monic, \pi _b   h = \pi _b k. Now the universal property of the pullback says
  that there is a unique morphism Z\to  P completing the diagram




